== Status text ==

In the article [[Western Roman Empire]], the status text of the infobox clearly shows it as the "Provinces of the [[Roman Empire]] governed by the Western Court". Similarly for this article, it should show the Byzantine Empire as the "Provinces of the Roman Empire governed by the Eastern Court (330-476)" when it coexisted with the Western Roman Empire (and perhaps with added status text "Sole court of the Roman Empire (476-1453)" for the later periods). In order to be consistent, the status text should either be shown in both articles (the preferred solution), or shown in neither articles. Thanks. --[[User:Cartakes|Cartakes]] ([[User talk:Cartakes|talk]]) 16:24, 11 September 2015 (UTC)
: [[WP:OTHERSTUFFEXISTS|OTHERCRAPEXISTS]]. I don't care what the [[Western Roman Empire]] article does. Consistency is not a priority here; the only thing that matters is that each article does what locally makes sense. Putting "provinces governed by the eastern court" in the box here makes no sense, because the period label "Byzantine" conventionally refers ''primarily'' and prototypically to the time when there was no western court to contrast it with (which was true for at least 90% of the time we call Byzantine even by the widest defintion of this term, if not for 100% of the time, depending on where you draw the line). The "Western" and the "Eastern" empire are not historically symmetrical entities and never were; that's why it really makes no sense to impose artificial uniformity on the way we present them. As for the second addition ("sole court 476-1453"), that would at least make it not entirely factually wrong, but the two entries together are clumsy, unwieldy, pedantic and simply not the kind of stuff that should be in infoboxes, whose first and only priority must be to remain crisp and brief. There simply is no cmpelling reason at all why any of this should be in the infobox in the first place, these are things that must be presented in proper text. [[User:Future Perfect at Sunrise|Fut.Perf.]] [[User talk:Future Perfect at Sunrise|☼]] 16:36, 11 September 2015 (UTC)
:: The [[Byzantine Empire]] in fact had two periods of different nature: 1. as part of the Roman Empire, from 330 to 476; 2. as a standalone empire from 476 onward. There is an important relationship between the Byzantine Empire and the Roman Empire, which should be listed in the infobox similar to other articles such as the [[Western Roman Empire]] even if we don't consider the Byzantine Empire and the Western Roman Empire as historically symmetrical entities. With this two lines as the status text for this article, it would be much clearer to readers about the actual nature of the Byzantine Empire by simply looking at this even if we don't talk about consistency with the [[Western Roman Empire]] article here. Furthermore, it is definitely not clumsy or unwieldy to list both. Look at articles such as [[Joseon]], it is in fact a commonplace in Wikipedia to list such texts in the infobox. --[[User:Cartakes|Cartakes]] ([[User talk:Cartakes|talk]]) 16:47, 11 September 2015 (UTC)

Just for reference: this text was first added by [[User:Jack Gaines]] on 11 April 2015 [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Byzantine_Empire&diff=656006242&oldid=655945339], then removed (by me) on 26 April [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Byzantine_Empire&diff=659344842&oldid=659344658], then reinserted by [[User:Cartakes]] on 27 June [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Byzantine_Empire&diff=668920281&oldid=668451600], then removed by [[User:Swarm]] on 15 August [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Byzantine_Empire&diff=676148369&oldid=676025230], then reinserted and expanded again by Cartakes on 16 August [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Byzantine_Empire&diff=676423297&oldid=676342538], then removed again by me on 7 September [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Byzantine_Empire&diff=679851937&oldid=679851763], then re-added once again by [[User:I Feel Tired]] [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Byzantine_Empire&diff=680127329&oldid=679851995] and twice more by Cartakes [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Byzantine_Empire&diff=680549439&oldid=680174086][https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Byzantine_Empire&diff=680552670&oldid=680552438], with reverts back by myself and most recently by [[User:Dr.K.]] [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Byzantine_Empire&diff=680553450&oldid=680552670]. None of the three people who inserted it made even a single talkpage contribution here during all that time, until today. What a fucking pathetic story. [[User:Future Perfect at Sunrise|Fut.Perf.]] [[User talk:Future Perfect at Sunrise|☼]] 17:02, 11 September 2015 (UTC)
