@[[User:Future Perfect at Sunrise|Fut.Perf.]], with all due respect, information like that on infoboxes are required. I was the one who reintroduced the "today part of..." under an IP address, which by the way I'm not giving, before creating a new account. I regret not using consensus before reintroducing "today part of..." infobox. Other empire and country articles like the [[Russian Empire]] and the [[Spanish Empire]] have a "today part of.." entry too.  <!-- Template:Unsigned --><small class="autosigned">—&nbsp;Preceding [[Wikipedia:Signatures|unsigned]] comment added by [[User:Kevinmuniz115|Kevinmuniz115]] ([[User talk:Kevinmuniz115#top|talk]] • [[Special:Contributions/Kevinmuniz115|contribs]]) </small> <!--Autosigned by SineBot-->

